{"questionId":"31769516","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Olivia’s house consists of four vertical walls and a sloping roof made from two rectangles. The height, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{CD}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>CD</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, from the ground to the base of the roof is 4.5 m.</p>\n<p>The base angles of the roof are <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{A}}\\mathop {\\text{B}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{C}} = 27^\\circ \">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>A</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>B</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>∧</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>C</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msup>\n    <mn>27</mn>\n    <mo>∘</mo>\n  </msup>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{A}}\\mathop {\\text{C}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{B}} = 26^\\circ \">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>A</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>C</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>∧</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>B</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msup>\n    <mn>26</mn>\n    <mo>∘</mo>\n  </msup>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/11d726ebf724779378ad11ab96ea9ccddff3e9ce.png\"></p>\n<p>The&nbsp;house is 10 m long and 5 m wide.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The length <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{AC}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>AC</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is approximately 2.84 m.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the total area of the two rectangles that make up the roof.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>Units are required in this question part.</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>10 × 2.84 + 10 × 2.74450…&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for finding their area of each rectangle and <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for adding their areas.</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>10 × (2.84 + 2.74450…)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for adding <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{AC}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>AC</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and their <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{AB}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>AB</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>. Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for multiplying their total area by 10.</p>\n<p>55.8 (55.8450…) m<sup>2</sup>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em><strong>(ft)</strong><em><strong>(G3)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Follow through from their <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{AB}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>AB</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> in part (a).</p>\n<p><strong><em>[3 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"31769516","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ1.T_2b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the total area of the two rectangles that make up the roof.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Prior learning","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, distance, midpoints","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}